    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#Crossing</IRI>
        <Literal>COLREG, rule 15: When two power-driven vessels are crossing so as to involve risk of collision, the vessel which has the other on her own starboard side shall keep out of the way and shall, if the circumstances of the case admit, avoid crossing ahead of the other vessel.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#HeadOn</IRI>
        <Literal>COLREG, rule 14: (a) When two power-driven vessels are meeting on reciprocal or nearly reciprocal courses so as to involve risk of collision each shall alter her course to starboard so that each shall pass on the port side of the other.
(b) Such a situation shall be deemed to exist when a vessel sees the other ahead or nearly ahead and by night she could see the masthead lights of the other in a line or nearly in a line and/or both sidelights and by day she observes the corresponding aspect of the other vessel.
(c) When a vessel is in any doubt as to whether such a situation exists she shall assume that it does exist and act accordingly.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#LightConfiguration</IRI>
        <Literal>Configuration of lights that vessels shall exhibits at night according to Part C of COLREG.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#LightConfiguration</IRI>
        <Literal>Light Configuration</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#LightConfigurationForNonTrawlingVesselEngagedInFishingDistancing</IRI>
        <Literal>Portion of the configuration of lights that a vessel engaged in fishing which is not trawling shall exhibit at night visible when the vessel is moving far from the observer.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#LightConfigurationForNonTrawlingVesselEngagedInFishingDistancing</IRI>
        <Literal>Light Configuration For a Non Trawling Vessel Engaged In Fishing Distancing</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#LightConfigurationForNonTrawlingVesselEngagedInFishingMovingCloser</IRI>
        <Literal>Portion of the configuration of lights that a vessel engaged in fishing which is not trawling shall exhibit at night visible when the vessel is moving towards to the observer.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#LightConfigurationForNonTrawlingVesselEngagedInFishingMovingCloser</IRI>
